ACT:
 Bombay Cinemas (Regulation) Act 11 of 1953 and Rules--Rule 89 does not prohibit construction of cinema building before grant of no objection certificate by Licensing Authority- Direction given by State Government to Licensing Authority vitiated if there is no application of mind to facts- Appellate order under s. 8A must give reasons--Use of words 'absolute discretion' in s. 5(2) of Chapter If does not invest State Government with arbitrary power.
 
